# Lab / compose: Kitchen API → Jupiter operator control plane (DV-077 / DV-072)
# Copy into your .env next to docker-compose and set values for your Jupiter host.
#
# KITCHEN_JUPITER_CONTROL_BASE — BlackBox api (server-side) → Sean Jupiter HTTP.
# Prefer the INTERNAL hostname:port for this hop (same lab LAN / corp DNS), e.g.
#   http://clawbot.a51.corp:707
# so Kitchen does not depend on public DNS or hairpin routes. Use the same Sean
# process the operator UI uses (internal and external names usually resolve to the
# same listener; internal is the right default for api → Jupiter).
#
# Wrong host (e.g. http://127.0.0.1:8080) = BlackBox api, not Sean — policy mismatch.
KITCHEN_JUPITER_CONTROL_BASE=
# Token must match Sean's JUPITER_OPERATOR_TOKEN (same as Kitchen → Jupiter POST Bearer).
KITCHEN_JUPITER_OPERATOR_TOKEN=
